  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a medium saucepan, rinse quinoa and cook with 2 cups of water until tender and the liquid is absorbed.",
    "Transfer quinoa to an oven-safe baking dish. Mix in chopped red bell pepper, nutritional yeast, smoked paprika, cumin, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Drizzle olive oil over the mixture and pour water evenly on top.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes until crispy and golden brown.",
    "Serve hot as a main course or side dish."
